cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on reinforcement learning (RL) and neural architecture search (NAS), which are both subfields of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions mobile robotics, which suggests that it may fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image-based RL tasks, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper uses evolutionary strategies (ES) for optimization, which is a subfield of neural evolution (NE), making cs.NE a possible category as well.
